# TMDB API Configuration
# Get your free API key from: https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api

# Backend (Rust/Tauri) - Required for API calls
TMDB_API_KEY=your_tmdb_api_key_here

# Frontend (Vite) - Optional, if you need to access the key in frontend code
# Note: Variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the browser
# VITE_TMDB_API_KEY=your_tmdb_api_key_here

# Development Notes:
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Replace 'your_tmdb_api_key_here' with your actual TMDB API key
# 3. Never commit .env to version control (it's in .gitignore)
# 4. The backend reads TMDB_API_KEY from the environment via std::env
# 5. Frontend can access VITE_* variables via import.meta.env.VITE_TMDB_API_KEY
